-- Kansai Electric to Extend Use of 40-Year-Old Mihama Reactor, Kyodo Says
-- Fergus Maguire
-- 2010-06-27T21:45:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-27/kansai-electric-to-extend-use-of-40-year-old-mihama-reactor-kyodo-says.html

          
          
             Kansai Electric Power Co. plans to 
extend the operation of the 40-year-old No. 1 reactor at the 
Mihama nuclear power plant for another 10 years, which would 
make it the longest operating Japanese reactor, Kyodo News 
reported, citing unidentified sources.  
          
          


  


        